{{dicdef}}

'''Katundu''' is a general [[mass noun]] for a group of items or [[matter]].

It may also refer to:
* [[luggage or baggage]] any number of bags, cases and containers which hold a traveller's articles during transit.

'''Origin'''
Katundu is a [[Bantu]] word found in the [[language]] of [[Chichewa]] which is widely spoken in south-central Africa.

'''Usage'''
...he said so much "katundu" (baggage) was lifted from his shoulders That he felt light enough to just flap...

Katundu is one of the less forgotten words of the Chichewa language used by foreigners. They will adapt it into there own native languages as its everyday usefulness (mass noun) makes it hard to forget it.